deck: Inker, sketch card artist and illustrator.
description:
Diana is a professional inker who has worked for several publishers including IDW and Marvel, providing inks on The Illegitimates, X-Men Legacy, Herc, Nova, and other titles.

She also produces sketch card illustrations, mostly on a licensed basis for trading card companies such as Upper Deck, Cryptozoic and Breygent. She has contributed original sketch work to over a dozen trading card sets to date, including DC, Marvel, and Dynamite properties.

Diana also illustrates her own pinup art, trading cards, and other collectibles.
name: Diana Greenhalgh

description:
Career

Andie Tong began his work in the comics industry in the early 2000s with work on titles such as The Spectacular Spider-Man, Batman Strikes!, Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles and Noble Causes. He also did some cover work for Blade of the Immortals, Bloodrayne and Twilight Men. In 2000 he created the graphic novel The Architect alongside writer Mike Baron. In 2010 he worked on a graphic novel entitled Tron: Betrayal. He is currently working on the art for the comic book version of Robert Jordan's Wheel of Time series. He also works for HarperCollins as an illustrator for children's picture books. 

Personal Life

Tong currently resides in London, England.
name: Andie Tong

description:
Career

Kieran Oats became involved in the comics industry in 2005 when he coloured the first issue of The Pact for ShadowLine. Over the next several years he did work, mostly as a colourist and occasionally as a cover artist, for companies including Dabel Brothers Productions, Zenescope, Marvel, Boom!, and Hasbro, among others. He ceased pursuing full-time work in comics in 2009. Following this, he has done occasional work for companies including Dynamite Entertainment, Atlas Comics, and Ardden Entertainment, among others.  

Personal Life

Oats was born in 1983 in Whakatane, New Zealand and raised in Edgecumbe. He spent some time in Melbourne, Australia, and currently lives in Awakeri, New Zealand.
name: Kieran Oats

deck: Robert Venditti is a  New York Times best-selling author. He is the writer of X-O Manowar and Green Lantern as well as a co-writer of the Flash
description:
Comics

Robert Venditti is the writer of Valiant's smash hit series X-O Manowar (2012). He is also the current writer of DC's New 52 Green Lantern (2011) and is co-writing The Flash (2011) with Van Jensen. He is best known for his graphic novel, The Surrogates from Top Shelf Productions and has also done some work for Marvel in Marvel Comics Presents #6 (2008).

Personal Life

Robert Venditti received a B.A. in Political Science and English from the University of Florida and an M.A. in Creative Writing from the University of Central Florida. He currently resides in Atlanta, Georgia where he continues his writing.

description: Rafa Garres studied at the Massana Art School and at the Faculty of Arts in Barcelona. Since then, Garres has worked for publishers like DC Comics, Fleetway and Crusade, cooperating with writers like Alan Grant, Pat Mills and John Wagner on series like Lobo, Sláine, Judge Dredd, Jaguar God, The Spectre and JLA. Rafa Garres is also an illustrator and painter. In 2005, he took over the artwork of the Mortepierre series from Muhamed Aoumri at Soleil Productions (scripts by Brice Tarvel).

He co-created The Alien Legion, which was optioned by Jerry Bruckheimer and Disney Studio Entertainment in January 2007. He is also the author of four science fiction and fantasy graphic novels.
